Class SocialContract

Provides utility constant values for using SocialProvider.

Please read information about how to use content providers in Android in order to learn how to use this contract. You can start by going into this page at Android developers site.

Note that this contract is currently the only documentation of SocialProvider on Android.

Author:
Babak dot Farshchian at sintef dot no

Field Detail

AUTHORITY_STRING

public static final java.lang.String AUTHORITY_STRING
The base URI used when calling SocialProvider.

You can use AUTHORITY_STRING with a field in SocialContract.UriPathIndex in order to build a URI for your queries to SocialProvider, e.g.:

query(Uri.parse(SocialContract.AUTHORITY_STRING+SocialContract.UriPathIndex.ME),....)
